---
import Footer from "@/components/Footer";
import "../styles/global.css";
import { ArrowLeft } from "lucide-react";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Privacy Policy | MVP Geek</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Privacy Policy for MVP Geek — how we collect, use, share and protect personal data for founders using our MVP building services."
    />
    <meta name="author" content="Rajesh Rajasekaran" />
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
    <meta name="googlebot" content="index, follow" />

    <!-- Canonical URL -->
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.mvpgeek.com/" />

    <!-- Favicon -->
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <!-- Fonts -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bricolage+Grotesque:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>

  <body
    class="min-h-screen leading-relaxed bg-[#0D0A08] text-white font-inter"
  >
    <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto space-y-6 py-12 px-4">
      <a href="/" class="py-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-lg"><ArrowLeft className="ml-2" size={20} />Back</a>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm opacity-80">Last updated: November 13, 2025</p>

      <p>
        At <strong>MVP Geek</strong> ("we", "our", "us") we respect your privacy
        and are committed to protecting the personal information you share with us.
        This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, why we collect
        it, how we use it, who we share it with, and your rights in relation to your
        information.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        1. Scope
      </h2>
      <p>
        This policy applies to information collected through our website <a
          class="underline text-white"
          href="https://www.mvpgeek.com">mvpgeek.com</a
        >, communications you send to us (for example, email or contact forms),
        and services we provide to clients.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        2. Information We Collect
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Contact & Identity Data:</strong> name, email address, phone number,
          company name and role when you contact us or request a quote.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Project Data:</strong> details you share about your idea, project
          requirements, and files you upload to us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage & Analytics:</strong> pages you visit on our site, IP address,
          browser type, device information and other standard analytics data collected
          via cookies and similar technologies.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Payment & Billing:</strong> if you purchase services, we collect
          invoicing details and payment transaction data (payments are processed
          by third-party payment processors — see section 6).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        3. How We Use Your Information
      </h2>
      <p>We use personal information for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          To respond to inquiries, provide quotes, and deliver our services.
        </li>
        <li>
          To communicate updates about projects, invoices, and support requests.
        </li>
        <li>
          To improve our website and services using analytics and performance
          data.
        </li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations and protect our legal rights.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        4. Legal Basis for Processing
      </h2>
      <p>
        Where applicable (for residents of jurisdictions with data protection
        laws such as the EU/UK), we rely on the following legal bases to process
        personal data: your consent, performance of a contract with you, our
        legitimate business interests (for example to operate and improve our
        services), and compliance with legal obligations.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        5. Cookies & Tracking
      </h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to provide site
        functionality, analyse usage, and personalise your experience. You can
        manage cookie preferences in your browser, or use our cookie controls
        where provided. For more details, see our
        <a class="underline text-white" href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        6. Third-Party Services & Data Sharing
      </h2>
      <p>
        We may share information with service providers who perform services on
        our behalf, such as hosting providers, analytics platforms, email
        providers, and payment processors. These parties only receive the
        information necessary to perform their services and are contractually
        required to protect your data.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may also disclose information if required by law or in response to
        lawful requests by public authorities.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        7. Data Transfers
      </h2>
      <p>
        Our systems may store and process data in countries outside your own.
        When we transfer personal data across borders we take steps to ensure it
        is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy (for
        example through standard contractual clauses where required).
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        8. Data Retention
      </h2>
      <p>
        We retain personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes
        described in this policy, to comply with legal obligations, resolve
        disputes, and enforce our agreements. If you would like us to delete
        your data earlier, please see
      </p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
